The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Bank of Rajasthan has registered an after-tax profit of Rs 5.22 crore for the first three months of the current financial year compared with Rs 20.15 crore recorded in the corresponding quarter last year. Total income fell marginally to Rs 155.08 crore from Rs 155.43 crore. The interest income has increased to Rs 135.42 crore from Rs 130.07 crore. The provisioning of Rs 4.42 crore for employees? wages and a depreciation of Rs 12 crore on investment in government securities has impacted its earnings.

 Sutlej Industries has posted a 100.77 per cent increase in net profit at Rs 2.61 crore for the three months ended June 30 against Rs 1.30 crore achieved in the same quarter last year. The turnover grew to Rs139.82 crore from Rs124.44. The company is diversifying into home textile and garments and has earmarked Rs 62 crore for the expansion. 

 UTI Bank has tied up with VISA International to offer pre-paid mobile customers, who are also a VISA cardholder, the facility to refill their mobile cards at any of the 1667 ATMs of UTI Bank and on the bank?s website ? www.utibank.com ? anytime and anywhere. VISA cardholders in the country, irrespective of the issuing bank, can now access UTI Bank ATMs and its website to refill their mobile cards across all cellular service providers. 

 HCL Comnet and Trend Micro have joined hands to offer a remote antivirus management solution, called Expert Service Offering. This is the first such end-to-end expert service delivered remotely which will proactively fortify enterprises from malicious virus attacks. Approximately one million enterprise users are expected to benefit from this service in the first year alone. 

 Hindustan Construction Company (HCC) has declared a 72 per cent increase in net profit for the first quarter of the current financial year at Rs 22.66 crore compared with the corresponding period last year. The turnover was recorded at Rs 479.43 crore, up 26% from Rs 380 crore clocked in the same quarter in 2004-05. 

 Shasun Chemicals and Drugs has reported a net profit of Rs 4.26 crore during the three months period ended June 30, up 8.67 per cent from Rs 3.92 crore in corresponding quarter last year. Revenues rose by 13.02 per cent to Rs 77.26 crore. The shareholders of the company have approved the splitting of company?s shares from the nominal face value of Rs 10 per share to Rs 2 each. 

 Sterling Tools has announced a consolidated net profit of Rs 1.82 crore for the first quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 1.26 crore in the same quarter last year. Revenues rose by 25 per cent to Rs 31.89 crore from Rs 25.60 crore.

